en demonstrated against several viral strains, is attributed to the action of triterpenoids and glycosides, which interfere with viral replication and entry into host cells.", "constituents": [], "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Chrysanthemum fisherae are sesquiterpenes, particularly fisheranol, isofisheranol, and fisheranone, which have been shown to exhibit antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties. These compounds have been isolated and characterized through chromatography and spectroscopy techniques, demonstrating their potential therapeutic applications. Additionally, Chrysanthemum fisherae contains flavonoids such as fisetin, quercetin, and kaempferol, which possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, helping to protect against oxidative stress and inflammation. The plant also contains phenolic acids like caffeic acid and ferulic acid, which have been reported to have antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties. Furthermore, the sesquiterpenes in Chrysanthemum fisherae have been found to have inhibitory effects on the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines, contributing to its potential therapeutic benefits.", "herb_names_common": [], "preparations": [{"name": "chrysanthemum tea", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 199, "total_score": 3980}, {"name": "tincture", "mentions": 18, "confidence_score": 115, "total_score": 2070}, {"name": "infusion", "mentions": 13, "confidence_score": 111, "total_score": 1443}, {"name": "decoction", "mentions": 16, "confidence_score": 100, "total_score": 1600}, {"name": "salve", "mentions": 14, "confidence_score": 63, "total_score": 882}, {"name": "infused oil", "mentions": 7, "confidence_score": 42, "total_score": 294}, {"name": "chrysanthemum infusion", "mentions": 2, "confidence_score": 18, "total_score": 36}, {"name": "chrysanthemum wine", "mentions": 2, "confidence_score": 17, "total_score": 34}, {"name": "glycerite", "mentions": 4, "confidence_score": 1